        public boolean isWinningBet​(Slot slot)

        eg. True if the betType is BetType.BLACK and the slots color is SlotColor.BLACK

        Specified by:

      • getOutcome

        public int getOutcome​(Slot slot)
        Description copied from interface: Bet
        Returns the outcome of the bet based on the supplied slot parameter.

        If the bet is a winning bet then the outcome will be a positive number based on the bet amount and the odds appropriate for the bet type. Otherwise the outcome will be a negative of the magnitude of the bet amount. Only Bet.NO_BET (declared below) should return an outcome of 0.

        Specified by:
        getOutcome in interface Bet
        Parameters:
        slot - the winning slot
        Returns:
        the outcome of the bet
        See Also:
        Bet.isWinningBet(Slot), BetType, BetType.getMultiplier()

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Description copied from interface: Bet
        Override Object.toString() Generates a string representing the bet as seen in the output trace. The following are examples of such strings (dependent on the concrete Bet class)
        • Bet 100 on Red
        • Bet 111 on Black
        • Bet 200 on Green
        • Bet 303 on Number 22
        • No Bet
        Note: The string includes the bet amount
        Note: The final example is produced as is in Bet.NO_BET
        Note: Green bet toString was not demonstrated in the output trace so will not be tested in A1.
        Note: You may find it useful to also override and use BetType.toString() to help produce these results.
